Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Line the internal & external corners of the RWU with a vertical 400mm wide strip of ADHERO, with min 150mm overlap on either side (option)

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Remove the 250mm release paper from the back of the ADHERO, and apply to RWU at a pre-marked height. Apply pressure using a PRESSFIX XL or rubber roller

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Remove the 2nd release paper, smooth down from centre of sheet, working outwards and applying pressure with a PRESSFIX XL or 150mm hard rubber roller

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Overlap ADHERO sheets in a shingle fashion working upwards. Observe sheet markings for 150mm overlap to all sheets, and to the edges of the RWU

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Work all air bubbles in ADHERO to sheet edge, and flatten all creases. (See 2.5b) Seal ADHERO to foundation surfaces with 5mm bead of ORCON sealant

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Remove both release papers from back of ADHERO and adhere from top down, following a pre marked vertical line

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Overlap sheets by 150mm min at vertical joins, and to the bottom edge of the RWU

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Firmly press ADHERO evenly across the sheet using PRESSFIX XL or rubber roller Work all air bubbles in ADHERO to sheet edge, and flatten all creases where possible

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Apply TESCON EXTORA 60mm tape to 100mm either side of any creases that terminate at the sheet edge or vertical overlap

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Cut ADHERO at 45° from the corners of all openings

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Fold ADHERO into all sides of the rough opening to the back edge of framing, and adhere to all sides using a PRESSFIX XL. Trim excess off

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Apply TESCON EXTOSEAL sill tape to the opening as per E2/AS1 (or as per designers project specific details)

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: For wet seal applications, apply TESCON WS foil tape to the full perimeter of the opening before window installation. Refer to the TESCON WS installation guide

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Ensure separation between ADHERO and Bitumen membranes at door sills/decks

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Use ROFLEX grommets and TESCON EXTORA 60 tape to seal all pipe penetrations made through the ADHERO. Refer to the ROFLEX installation guide

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Use KAFLEX grommets and TESCON EXTORA 60 tape to seal all round cable penetrations made through the ADHERO. Refer to the KAFLEX installation guide

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Use TESCON EXTORA 60 tape to seal all other penetrations made through the ADHERO that are not possible to seal with ROFLEX or KAFLEX grommets

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Repair all cuts and tears in ADHERO with TESCON EXTORA 100 tape, to a minimum 50mm past the edges of the damaged area.

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Repair larger holes in ADHERO with another piece of ADHERO, allowing for min 150mm cover past the damaged area on all sides. Then apply EXTORA 60mm tape across the top and sides of the ADHERO patch

Tier 1: Proclima Underlay Installation QA West Ground Floor
Tier 3: Seal screw penetrations through ADHERO from cladding attachments with TESCON NAIDECK butyl tape or EXTOSEAL sill tape. Discuss with the cladding/roofing installer before handing over areas to be clad.
